[{"id":"VH929582","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">At a large university, data were collected on the number of sisters and brothers that each student had. Let the random variable <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow></math></span></span> represent the number of sisters and the random variable <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>Y</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> represent the number of brothers. The distribution of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> has mean 1.00 and standard deviation 0.94. The distribution of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>Y</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> has mean 1.07 and standard deviation 1.04. What is the mean of the distribution of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X plus Y\"><math alttext=\"X plus Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>Y</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> ?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH929582_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">1.98</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">2.01</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">2.04</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">2.0528</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">2.07</p>"],"answer":4}]